- "Frequently used and highly accurate" refers to models with high counts of total accesses and average accuracy; 
- "Percentile rank" indicates the position of a model when sorted by total accesses or average accuracy, with 1 being the top percentile;
- "Unique users" implies counting distinct individuals who engaged with each model.

sql:
SELECT group_name, group_description
FROM demographic_groups
WHERE group_weight = (SELECT MAX(group_weight) FROM demographic_groups);

SELECT prediction, confidence
FROM model_predictions
ORDER BY confidence DESC;
